The 3 Part of the Maiku Hama Triology is the best and probably darkest of all the films. In fact, this episode is more of a horror-like thriller reminiscent of a Takashi Miike film. &quot;The Trap,&quot; which is the final film of the trilogy was preceded by the more semi-comical episodes of &quot;The Most Terrible Time In My Life,&quot; and then followed by &quot;Stairway To The Distant Past,&quot; and finally concluding with this film, &quot;The Trap.&quot; In the previous episodes of the trilogy, Maiku Hama (Masatoshi Nagase) is not the aloof private detective he was originally portrayed as; but a much more intelligent and calm detective.
